## 九、适用法律与争议解决 / 9. Governing Law & Dispute Resolution

本许可文件适用中华人民共和国法律。

因本许可文件产生的任何争议，双方应首先通过友好协商解决，
协商期限为六十（60）日。协商不成的，任一方可将争议提交
上海国际经济贸易仲裁委员会（SHIAC）按其届时有效的仲裁规则
进行仲裁，仲裁地为上海，仲裁语言为中文。
双方当事人均为外国实体，或经双方书面同意的，可将争议提交
新加坡国际仲裁中心（SIAC）按其届时有效的仲裁规则仲裁，
仲裁地为新加坡，仲裁语言为英文。
仲裁裁决是终局的，对双方均有约束力。

如争议事项依法不属于可仲裁范围，或仲裁裁决被有管辖权的法院
撤销或不予执行的，由作者住所地有管辖权的人民法院管辖。

This license is governed by the laws of the People's Republic of China.

Any dispute arising from or in connection with this license shall first
be resolved through amicable negotiation within sixty (60) days.
Failing that, either party may submit the dispute to the Shanghai
International Economic and Trade Arbitration Commission (SHIAC) for
arbitration in accordance with its then-effective rules, with the seat
in Shanghai and the language in Chinese.
If both parties are foreign entities, or by mutual written agreement,
the dispute may be submitted to the Singapore International Arbitration
Centre (SIAC) in accordance with its then-effective rules, with the
seat in Singapore and the language in English.
The arbitral award is final and binding on both parties.

If the subject matter of the dispute is not arbitrable by applicable
law, or if the arbitral award is set aside or refused enforcement by a
competent court, the competent court at the author's domicile shall
have jurisdiction.

